Two people have been killed and one in a critical condition after a vehicle and a truck collided on the N4, close to the Dr Moroka off-ramp in Rustenburg. Paramedics found a man and woman, believed to be husband and wife, were killed in the collision. ER24 Spokesperson Annine Siddall said, “Unfortunately, there was nothing paramedics could to do save their lives and they were declared dead on the scene”. She added, “A man, believed to be in his late 20s, sustained serious injuries and was transported to MediCare Rustenburg under advanced care”. The exact circumstances surrounding the collision are not yet known to our paramedics but local authorities were on the scene to investigate further. -TNA Reporter 